bio.experienceSummary: Hello! If you're looking for excellent care, Im the perfect match for you. Im an energetic and loving mother to a 2-year-old boy. I have lots of experience working with children from birth to 13 years old. In addition to caring for your little ones, Im able to do light house keeping and run errands for you!

description.originalText: Olivia was so great to have as a sitter for our 2 year old. As first time parents we were nervous about leaving our son, but she is respectful, professional and overall has a very calming personality. Definitely would recommend and hire her again.

bio.experienceSummary:
I have nine years of childcare experience and am known for being very professional and reliable. In addition, I am warm, caring, creative, honest, respectful, and organized.

I want to be your future nanny and become part of your family routine. I love sharing cultures, learning new things, and making great memories while improving my English skills

Thank you for taking the time to read my resume and looking forward to speaking further. I am ready to start as soon as you need me. References are available from the different families I have worked with.

More than 9 years of experience

3-12 months babysitting experienced.

Children and teenagers experience.

First-Aid certificate.

Vaccinated.

Enjoys arts & crafts.

Cooking.

Non-smoker.

Pet-friendly.

I'm a childcare provider with three years of experience who's passionate about nurturing children's growth and development. I'm dedicated to supporting families and providing a safe, stimulating environment for children to learn and thrive.

I'm patient, calm, and creative, and I have a knack for making learning fun. I believe in open communication with parents and will work with you to ensure your child's needs are met.

I enjoy playing a variety of games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games. I'm comfortable caring for children of all ages and have experience with infants, toddlers, preschoolers, and school-aged children. I also speak both English and Spanish.

I have my own car and am CPR and First Aid certified. I would be happy to provide references upon request.

I look forward to the opportunity to care for your child and help them reach their full potential.

Hi my name is scarlet I'm 19 years old I speak English and Spanish a devoted childcare provider with three years of experience, my passion lies in nurturing the growth and development of young minds. My patient and friendly nature creates a welcoming and comfortable environment for children. I believe in open communication with parents, providing daily written reports and engaging in verbal discussions during pickup. When it comes to enforcing household rules, I maintain a firm yet understanding approach.

From outdoor sports to educational games, I love incorporating a variety of activities that cater to different interests and promote learning. My fluency in both English and Spanish allows me to connect with a diverse range of families.

I'm seeking a position where I can share my love for caregiving and make a positive impact on a child's life. I am happy to assist with cooking and meal preparation.

Let's connect and explore how I can provide the best possible care for your child.

description.originalText: es una babysitter muy buena y sobre todo responsable con su trabajo y es muy puntual.

bio.experienceSummary: With over 10 years of experience caring for children ranging from newborns to teens, I am passionate about creating a safe, nurturing, and fun environment. In addition to childcare, I am comfortable assisting with light housekeeping and running errands to help make your day a little easier. Hi! My name is Bridget. I've been a middle and high school English teacher for 8 years, but I also have worked as a nanny and babysitter for a number of summers. Although I teach older students, I have taken a number of early childhood development courses, and I love working with little ones too! I also tutor (elementary, middle, and high school students), so if you wanted me to help your children keep up with academics over the summer after the effects of COVID-19 and at-home learning, I would be more than happy to do so!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello I'm Nairy !

I am fun loving, responsible and reliable! I have experience working with children through a number of my volunteer roles and work including babysitting. I am in my second year of college majoring in psychology. I speak Fluent English and Spanish!

 I really cherish the moments where I can help families support a child's growth. Just like children learn a lot from us we can learn just as much from them. I love tapping into my inner child and seeing the joy on their faces after every accomplishment. I love working with kids because it allows you to see growth and progress in amazing, measurable ways. 

I'd describe my personality as gentle, charismatic, outgoing and nurturing. In my spare time I like to go on runs , paint, as well as read, and watch the sunset on the beach!

Some of my valued skills are CPR certified , organization, planning , and creativity!

description.originalText:
Nairy was punctual, kind and helpful. She was sweet and engaging with the children. They looked forward to seeing her each week and enjoyed playing with her. 

Since we only saw her once a week, we didn't get a lot of time with her to give a more detailed review, hence the 4 stars.

I DO work a FT job so I am currently looking for something here and there or evenings.
